# ─── Privacy boundary: NEVER commit operator-private content ─────────────
#
# The hermes-dist repo is PUBLIC (or at least visible to all your users).
# The boundary is:
#
#   IN this repo (workflow / structure / config)        OUT of this repo
#   ──────────────────────────────────────────         ──────────────────
#   default-template/  (the user-facing bundle)        ~/.hermes/ (operator's own hermes)
#   relay/              (collector code)                ~/.hermes/mnemosyne/data/ (private memories)
#   docs/                                               ~/research/ (operator's research notes)
#   install-common/                                    ~/.hermes-dist-operator.env (operator tokens)
#   winget/                                            ~/.hermes-dist-keys/ (private keys)
#                                                       ~/hermes-dist-private/ (your dev branch)
#
# Rule of thumb: if it's "how the system works" → in this repo.
#                if it's "what I've done / found / remembered" → out.

# Operator's own hermes install
/.hermes/
/hermes-home/

# Mnemosyne private database
**/mnemosyne/data/
**/mnemosyne/data/*.db
**/mnemosyne/data/*.sqlite*

